(3 comments)

I want to take another look (wondering if this has any devstack implications).  Some suggested revisions inline.  (The release note could be updated as a follow-up patch.)

Patch Set 5:

I looked through devstack, looks like everything uses the tls-proxy for ssl termination, so this should be OK.  I put up a devstack patch depending on this change so we can see what happens:
https://review.opendev.org/#/c/698811/

Also noticed that devstack still has support for the v1 API, so I put up a patch to remove that: https://review.opendev.org/#/c/698808/

Patch Set 5:

tempest-full-py3 failed with this change on https://review.opendev.org/#/c/698811/ ... have not had time to determine whether it's a real or spurious failure.

Also, I just noticed that https://review.opendev.org/#/c/695707/ has not merged yet.  I just rebased it.  We need that to get all the tips jobs running on py3.

Patch Set 5:

(1 comment)

Patch Set 5: Code-Review+1

Another option would be to rely on the version of this in oslo.service instead. It's still broken on py3, but I guess everything could be... broken... together that way. Given that there's no more py2 releases and it's very unlikely that eventlet ever gets fixed, I think this is fine though.

Patch Set 5: Code-Review+2

Looks like that devstack patch tempest failure on https://review.opendev.org/#/c/698811/ was spurious.

Patch Set 5:

I think we should wait to merge this just in case the tests on that devstack weren't as thorough as I thought they were, because this change has the potential to break the gate.

I propose that Abhishek +W it when he comes in to work on Monday morning, and that way between Erno, me, and Sean, we'll have people available to revert the change in the worst case.
